<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>The King Fighters of Kyo is a spin-off from SNK's successful fighting games that focuses on the series main character: Kyo Kusanagi. The game was based on the comic book (same title) by a Japanese Artist,Natsumoto Masato. The difference, well, the main difference is the comic is based on the story of KOF96, and the game is base on KOF97.
        		<br><br>The game takes place 11 months after the '96 tournament, and covers the months prior to the '97 tournament and the tournament itself from an RPG-like point of view. You control Kyo, and go around the world (starting in your home, Osaka and eventually going to places like Mexico and California) advancing a plot line related to the Orochi storyline and your eternal enemy, Iori Yagami, by interacting with other characters from the series, solving subquests and winning fights viewed from a first-person perspective.
        		<br><br>Fights are turn-based, with a menu-based system from which you select actions and moves to execute. The overall objective of the game is to explore and learn everything you can about the back stories and subplots revolving each character, and get a pair of teammates (anyone from the 31 available characters, not just the "hero" team) and enough experience to enter the '97 tournament. Also included is a battle mode, and a sound test mode.
        		<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Play as Kyo Kusanagi searching to find a tag team with which to enter the next tournament. A team can be built up by befriending a character and helping them solve their particular plight. Plenty of fisticuffs along the way as familiar faces from the series such as Mai, Chris and Athena pop up. A real treat for fans of the series developed by Yumekobo. 
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>First & Third person perspectives.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Fighting theme.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

